@startuml Sequence_Customer_Registration

actor Customer
participant "Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Backend API" as API
database "Database" as DB

== Customer Registration ==

Customer -> Frontend: Access Registration Page
Frontend --> Customer: Display registration form

Customer -> Frontend: Fill Registration Form\n(name, email, password, phone)
Frontend -> Frontend: Validate form data

Customer -> Frontend: Submit Registration
Frontend -> API: POST /api/auth/register\n(name, email, password, phone, role="Customer")
API -> DB: Check if email exists
DB --> API: Email not found

API -> API: Hash password
API -> DB: Create User\n(role = "Customer",\nstatus = "Active")
DB --> API: User created

API -> DB: Create Customer record\n(link to user)
DB --> API: Customer created

API -> API: Generate JWT token
API --> Frontend: Registration success\n+ Auth token
Frontend --> Customer: Registration successful\nRedirect to dashboard

== Customer Login ==

Customer -> Frontend: Access Login Page
Frontend --> Customer: Display login form

Customer -> Frontend: Enter Credentials\n(email, password)
Customer -> Frontend: Submit Login
Frontend -> API: POST /api/auth/login\n(email, password)
API -> DB: Find user by email
DB --> API: User data

API -> API: Verify password
alt Valid Credentials
  API -> API: Generate JWT token
  API --> Frontend: Login success\n+ Auth token + User data
  Frontend -> Frontend: Store token
  Frontend --> Customer: Redirect to dashboard
else Invalid Credentials
  API --> Frontend: Error: Invalid credentials
  Frontend --> Customer: Error message
end

== Customer Profile Update ==

Customer -> Frontend: View Profile
Frontend -> API: GET /api/profile
API -> DB: Fetch user data
DB --> API: User data
API --> Frontend: Profile data
Frontend --> Customer: Display profile

Customer -> Frontend: Update Profile\n(address, phone, gender)
Frontend -> API: PUT /api/profile\n(updated fields)
API -> DB: Update user
DB --> API: User updated

API -> DB: Update customer record
DB --> API: Customer updated

API --> Frontend: Profile updated
Frontend --> Customer: Success message

note right of DB
  User Role: "Customer"
  Status: "Active"
  Linked to Customer record
end note

@enduml


